# Styling Guidelines

## TailwindCSS Rules

- Always use Tailwind classes for styling HTML elements.
- Avoid using CSS or `<style>` tags.
- Use "class:" instead of the ternary operator in class tags whenever possible.

## Style Best Practices

- Maintain consistent spacing and sizing using Tailwind utility classes.
- Use Tailwind's responsive modifiers for responsive design (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:, 2xl:).
- Leverage Tailwind's color palette and design tokens.
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS solutions.

## UI Component Library

- **Use shadcn/ui components** from `@/components/ui` for all standard UI patterns.
- Style shadcn components using Tailwind classes via the `className` prop.
- Leverage component variants (e.g., Button variants) before creating custom styles.
- Maintain consistency by using the established component library throughout the application.
